title: effective go: typos
body:
by **omeleet**: 
I'm not sure about the second one (being a non native english speaker).

1)
http://golang.org/doc/effective_go.html#blank_implements
"implementing the type that it it actually"
too many it

2)
http://golang.org/doc/effective_go.html#embedding
"there is no problem if a field is added that conflicts with"
I would rather say "there is no problem if an added field conflicts with [lorem
ipsum]"

In the hope that it will be useful.
